{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionEvent Detection (ED) is an essential yet challenging information extraction task in the field of Natural Language Processing.",
    "An event is identified by a word or a phrase called event trigger which most represents that event.",
    "Given an input text, ED aims to identify the event triggers and classify them into predefined event types.",
    "For instance, in the input sentence \"Stewart's 1979 marriage to Alana Hamilton lasted five years and produced two children.",
    "\", an ED model needs to recognize the word \"marriage\" as an event trigger and predict its event type as \"Life.Marry\".Early ED methods explored statistical information in the training sets and used patternbased methods [1][2][3]."
  ]
}